30/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Parliament Speaker and interim President Natasa Micic expressed hope that she would keep her post, following debate in parliament Wednesday (29 October) on an upcoming vote of confidence. 
A debate on the confidence vote for the government is to start Thursday. 
Only after this debate would votes of confidence on the speaker and the government be scheduled.
In other news Wednesday, Gerhard Schroeder arrived in Belgrade, the first visit by a German chancellor in 18 years. 
Meeting with senior politicians, he expressed strong support for Serbia-Montenegro's Euro-Atlantic drive but urged more efforts aimed at attracting foreign investors. 
(Blic, B92, BBC, FoNet, Tanjug, AFP - 29/10/03)
